<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="77" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1177,1347]" pageId="16" pageNumber="77">
Hundreds of species in the Old World have been described in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="(Andre 1902 b)" baseAuthorityName="Andre" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[983,1244,1177,1204]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Mutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[983,1065,1177,1203]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="77">Mutilla</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Andre, E." box="[1082,1237,1177,1204]" pageId="16" pageNumber="77" pagination="1 - 77" refId="ref16224" refString="Andre, E. (1902 b [&quot; 1903 &quot;]) Fam. Mutillidae. In: Wytsman, P., Genera Insectorum. Fasc. 11. L. Desmet-Verteneuil, Bruxelles, pp. 1 - 77, 3 pls." type="journal article" year="1902">André 1902b</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but they belong to different genera, and even to different tribes and subfamilies. 
<taxonomicName box="[894,1067,1213,1239]" pageId="16" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis box="[894,976,1213,1239]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="77">Mutilla</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
were recently catalogued in the Palaearctic (ten species— 
<bibRefCitation author="Lelej, A. S." box="[441,566,1249,1275]" pageId="16" pageNumber="77" refId="ref18082" refString="Lelej, A. S. (2002) Catalogue of the Mutillidae (Hymenoptera) of the Palaearctic Region. Dalnauka, Vladivostok, 172 pp." type="book" year="2002">Lelej 2002</bibRefCitation>
), and in the Oriental region (four species— 
<bibRefCitation author="Lelej, A. S." box="[1054,1179,1249,1276]" pageId="16" pageNumber="77" refId="ref18110" refString="Lelej, A. S. (2005) Catalogue of the Mutillidae (Hymenoptera) of the Oriental Region. Dalnauka, Vladivostok, 252 pp." type="book" year="2005">Lelej 2005</bibRefCitation>
), but have not been recently examined in the Afrotropical region (142 species— 
<bibRefCitation author="Bischoff, H. &amp; Monographie der Mutilliden Afrikas" box="[799,963,1285,1311]" pageId="16" pageNumber="77" refId="ref16504" refString="Bischoff, H. (1920 - 1921) Monographie der Mutilliden Afrikas. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 86 A (1 - 3 &amp; 4 - 5), 1 - 480 (1920) &amp; 481 - 830 (1921)." type="journal volume" year="1920">Bischoff 1920</bibRefCitation>
). Two species of this genus are distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[178,305,1321,1347]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="16" pageNumber="77">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
